<br>
A loud scream of pain was heard from her mouth and her entire armies eyes were turned.<br>
<br>
She glanced at her wolves.<br>
<br>
&quot;Keep the war going until they are dead. I am leaving you in charge.&quot; She glanced to her loyal wolf that had fought beside her.<br>
<br>
<br>
She stood up and mounted her horse riding towards the north.<br>
<br>
A whisper escaped her mouth.. . &quot;Hippolyte.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaeacuswolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeacus Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 11:24:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/heraqofgsmo/aeacus.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ··~§*·Centaur War·*§~·· The Eastern Forest</span><hr size=1> Aeacus heard his Queen's words, and howled to the wolves the message.  Growling he turned back to the Centaurs, who now were beginning to fear this large pack of wolves that had killed or wounded their brothers.  Aeacus lowered his head slowely stalking the Centaurs who began to back off.  Then with a lunge and a loud barking growl, all the wolves descended upon the Centaurs who were in the Eastern parts of the forest.  Eventually, the wolf pack killed all but those who ran away.  After feeling that the eastside had been won, he tilted his head up and sent the message of the win to Queen Alysia in a long howl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=scynthianwolf>Scynthian Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 11:42:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Here he comes a runnin</span><hr size=1> Scythe ran all the way from the healing hut towards the Eastern forest when he heard the howl of victory.. He approached Aeacus and looked him in the eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;The war is over Aeacus,&quot; His eyes dropped. <br>
<br>
&quot;The Queen is dead.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaeacuswolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeacus Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 11:54:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/heraqofgsmo/aeacus.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here he comes a runnin</span><hr size=1> Aeacus looked at Scythe in almost disbelief.  He glanced back at the other wolves who were now gathering around, and then back to Scythe.  <br>
>>Take us to her<< <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=scynthianwolf>Scynthian Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 12:00:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> They went to Themiscrya</span><hr size=1> He nodded to the wolf who just happened to be the leader of the wolves. How could Scythe not say yes?<br>
<br>
They all ran towards the healing hut and then as they stepped through the door they saw them. <br>
<br>
Scythe wandered through the door looking at Hippolyte and Aly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gods. . .&quot;<br>
